<HL>
   Business Brief -- Modine Manufacturing Co.:
   Rise of 5% to 10% Expected
   For Fiscal Year Sales, Profit
</HL>
<DATE>
06/11/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6A
</SO>
<CO>
   MODI
</CO>
<LP>
   Modine Manufacturing Co., Racine, Wis., said its sales and
earnings for the fiscal year ending March 31, 1991, are
expected to rise 5%-to-10% over the previous year.
   For the year ended March 31, 1990, Modine earned $25.2
million, or $1.68 a share, on sales of $436.3 million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The maker of automotive parts and heating and
air-conditioning equipment said its outlook for the new year
indicates a stronger automotive aftermarket. Modine also said
it expects more growth in its heavy-duty and industrial
businesses, as well as continued strength in its heating and
ventilating business and its international activities.
</TEXT>
